Cocoa Exports From Ivory Coast’s San Pedro Port Rise in June

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-07-07T18:09:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/cocoa-exports-from-ivory-coast-s-san-pedro-port-rise-in-june.html
Exports of  cocoa beans  from Ivory
Coast’s port of San Pedro increased to 83,594 metric tons in
June from 20,078 tons a year earlier, the harbor said.  Shipments of cocoa liquor rose 70 percent to 8,815 tons
from 5,188 tons while exports of chocolate increased to 1,184
tons from last year’s 1,011 tons, according to an e-mailed
statement today. Exports of cocoa cake were 202 tons, the
document showed.  Coffee exports rose to 179 tons from 94 tons last year,
according to the statement. Rubber exports dropped 25 percent to
7,252 tons and shipments of  palm oil  jumped to 28,830 tons from
5,000 tons a year ago, it showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Olivier Monnier in Abidjan via Accra at
   ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 